title: Textile, 1995-50-120, ca. 1770
medium:
Cotton, plain weave.
Printed by engraved plate.
description: Complex and busy pattern that includes people banqueting at a dais, a man and a woman jousting from boats, a tower with a seated couple beside it, bacchus in a chariot, nymphs ornamenting a herm, chinoiserie and scenes of feasting.
